reviewText: Came when promised. Movie quality varied though. Would give 5 stars for interesting Alfred Hitchcock early movies, otherwise.
Very, very old movies most of them.
A nice collection of early films.

I cannot tell  you the disappointment when we were half way through Jamaica Inn and the film suddenly skipped to the end. Useless. What do you do - buy another copy? This was only the second movie we watched in the collection. It quite puts you off even trying with the others. We got a refund, but what a waste of time. No need these days for faulty goods to be sold like this.

Alfred Hitchcock is one of the best known and most popular filmmakers ever. This 3 (not 2) DVD set includes:
1 The Lady Vanishes
2 Sabotage
3 Blackmail
4 Jamaica Inn
5 Number 17
6 The 39 Steps
7 The Man Who Knew Too Much
8 The Secret Agent
9 Murder
10 Young & Innocent
11 Juno and The Paycock
12 The Skin Game
13 Rich and Strange
14 The Farmer's Wife
15 The Manxman
